# Netlify cache rules. The entry HTML and the JS module graph are NOT content-hashed,
# so a browser/CDN could otherwise keep serving an old build after you redeploy — the
# classic "my phone still shows the old version" problem. Force them to revalidate every
# load (ETag → tiny 304 when unchanged), so a fresh deploy always wins immediately.
# Static art in /assets keeps normal caching.
/index.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
/src/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
